# clean up

train_df <- train_df |> 
  # rename(threessnPorch = `3SsnPorch`) |> 
  mutate(Alley = as.character(Alley),
         Alley = replace_na(Alley, "No ally access"),
         Alley = as.factor(Alley)) |> 
  mutate(GarageQual = as.character(GarageQual),
         GarageQual = replace_na(GarageQual, "No Garage"),
         GarageQual = as.factor(GarageQual)) |> 
  mutate(GarageType = as.character(GarageType),
         GarageType = replace_na(GarageType, "No Garage"),
         GarageType = as.factor(GarageType)) |> 
  mutate(FireplaceQu = as.character(FireplaceQu),
         FireplaceQu = replace_na(FireplaceQu, "No fireplace"),
         FireplaceQu = as.factor(FireplaceQu)) |> 
  mutate(BsmtCond = as.character(BsmtCond),
         BsmtCond = replace_na(BsmtCond, "No basement"),
         BsmtCond = as.factor(BsmtCond)) |> 
  mutate(BsmtQual = as.character(BsmtQual),
         BsmtQual = replace_na(BsmtQual, "No basement"),
         BsmtQual = as.factor(BsmtQual)) |> 
  mutate(BsmtExposure = as.character(BsmtExposure),
         BsmtExposure = replace_na(BsmtExposure, "No fireplace"),
         BsmtExposure = as.factor(BsmtExposure)) |> 
  mutate(TotalSF = X1stFlrSF + X2ndFlrSF + BsmtUnfSF + TotalBsmtSF + WoodDeckSF + OpenPorchSF + EnclosedPorch + ScreenPorch + PoolArea + GarageArea ,
                RichNbrhd = case_when(Neighborhood %in% c("StoneBr", "NridgHt", "NoRidge") ~ 1,
                                                          TRUE ~ 0)) |> 
  mutate(PoolQC = as.character(PoolQC),
         PoolQC = replace_na(PoolQC, "No Pool"),
         PoolQC = as.factor(PoolQC)) |> 
  mutate( # "housing_crisis" for outliers (Dec 2007 - Jun 2009)
    
    Housing_Crisis = case_when(
      (YrSold == 2007 & MoSold == 12) |
      (YrSold == 2008) |
      (YrSold == 2009 & MoSold <= 6) ~ 1,
      TRUE ~ 2
    )
  ) |> 
  mutate(TotalSF2 = X1stFlrSF + X2ndFlrSF + TotalBsmtSF)

Interpretation of Model

This log-linear model for SalePrice incorporates both continuous variables (like TotalSF, GrLivArea, YearRemodAdd, GarageCars, and Fireplaces) and categorical variables (such as KitchenQual, BsmtQual, PoolQC, and Neighborhood), with interactions between TotalSF and quality measures. Because the response is log(SalePrice), each coefficient approximates the percentage change in sale price for a one-unit change in the predictorfor instance, each additional square foot of GrLivArea is associated with about a 0.02% increase in price, while the negative TotalSF coefficient suggests that, when controlling for GrLivArea, extra non-living area slightly detracts from value. The categorical variables indicate how different quality levels and neighborhoods deviate from a reference category, with lower quality ratings in kitchens and basements significantly reducing price.

The model explains about 85.8% of the variation in log sale prices rounded (Adjusted R = 0.86) and has a low residual standard error, signaling a strong fit. Significant interactions reveal that the impact of additional square footage is enhanced in homes with higher kitchen or overall quality. Meanwhile, neighborhood effects varysome areas are associated with higher prices, while others are linked to lower values. Overall, the model effectively captures the complex relationships between property features, quality, and location in determining house prices.

Validation

set.seed(90)
num_rows <- 1000 #1460 total
keep <- sample(1:nrow(train_df), num_rows)
mytrain <- train_df[keep, ] #Use this in the lm(..., data=mytrain)
mytest <- train_df[-keep, ] #Use this in the predict(..., newdata=mytest)

yh_hd <- predict(final.lm, newdata=mytest)
ybar <- (mean( log(mytest$SalePrice)))
SSTO <- sum( ( log(mytest$SalePrice) - ybar)^2 )
SSE_hd <- sum( ( log(mytest$SalePrice) - yh_hd)^2 )
rs_hd <- 1 - SSE_hd/SSTO
n <- nrow(mytest)
p_hd <- length(final.lm)
rsa_hd <- 1 - (n-1)/(n-p_hd)*SSE_hd/SSTO

# r-squared adjusted
# rsa_hd

adj_r2 <- round(summary(final.lm)$adj.r.squared, 2)
cat("Adjusted R-squared:", adj_r2, "\n")
## Adjusted R-squared: 0.86
rsa_hd_r2 <- round(rsa_hd, 2)
cat("Validation R-squared:", rsa_hd_r2, "\n")
## Validation R-squared: 0.84
# validation current: 0.8515619 GTG
# Adjusted R-squared: 0.8433
